Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @penne pasta{180%grams} to the water and bring back to the
boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and thinly slice the @onion{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @onion{1}(halved, peeled and thinly sliced), @British smoked
bacon lardons{90%grams} and @British beef mince{240%grams} and fry until the
onion has started to soften and the mince has browned, ~{7-9%minutes}. Use a
spoon to break the mince up as it cooks.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince. It's
> cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While everything cooks, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%grams}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the garlic to the mince and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @red wine stock paste{28%grams},
@Worcester sauce{15%grams}, @tomato ketchup{1%tbsp}, @sugar{1%tsp} and
@water{50%milliliters} for the sauce.

Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until thickened,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, add a drizzle of @olive oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @black pepper{}. Mix to combine the dressing.

Once the pasta sauce has thickened, stir in the @butter{20%grams} until melted.

When the pasta is cooked, stir it into the sauce.

Toss the @wild rocket{20%grams} through the dressing.

Share the pasta between your #serving bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the cheese. Drizzle over the @burger sauce{30%grams}.

Serve the rocket salad on the side. Enjoy!